article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 70, SIU-Edwardsville 59
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- James Eayrs notched career highs in points with 22 and rebounds with 12 as Wisconsin-Milwaukee defeated Southern Illinois-Edwardsville 70-59 Monday night. Tone Boyle added 15 points for the Panthers (10-6). The Cougars (5-13), in their first year in NCAA Division I, were led by John Edmison with 20 points and Barry Welington with 11. Edmison topped his previous high of 19 points at Southeast Missouri Dec. 31. Eayrs scored Milwaukee's last 10 points of the first half and put the Panthers ahead 31-27 at intermission with two baskets in the last 1:46. Edwardsville got within 33-32 on a two free throws by Aamir McCleary, but Milwaukee pulled away for good at 37-32 on two free throws by Boyle and two by Anthony Hill. Eayrs' previous highs were 15 points against Illinois-Chicago Dec. 30 and 8 rebounds against Wright State Dec. 6.
